SIMPLE: jobbing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jobbing
<hw>Job"bing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Doing
chance work or odd jobs; <as>as, a <ex>jobbing</ex>
carpenter</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Using opportunities of public service for private
gain; <as>as, a <ex>jobbing</ex> politician</as>.</def> <rj><au>London
Sat. Rev.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Jobbing house</b></col>, <cd>a mercantile establishment
which buys from importers, wholesalers or manufacturers, and sells to
retailers.</cd> <mark>[U.S.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>job control language</ent>⟦br⟧
